Privacy Policy
Effective date: Oct 25, 2019
This Privacy Policy explains what personal data is collected when you (you or User) use the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP mobile application (We) and the services provided through it (together the “Service”), and how this personal data will be used and shared.
Please read the Privacy Policy carefully before using our Service.  We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time and in this case, we will notify you about it. Our Terms of Service is available here https://www.smartfitnessapp.com/termsofservice/.
BY USING THE SERVICE, YOU AGREE AND ASSERT YOU HAVE READ, UNDERSTAND, AND AGREE TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY YOU ASSERT YOU ARE OF LEGAL AGE (18 YEARS OLD) 
If you disagree with these assertions and promises, you must (a) delete your account using the functionality found in “Settings” in the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP, or contact us and request deletion of your data; (b) cancel any subscriptions using the functionality provided by Apple (if you are using iOS) or Google (if you are using Android); and (c) delete the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP from your devices.

Definitions:
“Personally identifiable information” any data that could potentially be used to identify a particular person.
“GDPR” the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data.
“EEA” includes all current member states to the European Union and the European Economic Area.
“Process”, in respect of personal data, includes to collection, storage, and disclose to third parties.
1.	CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL DATA COLLECTED
1.1.	DATA PROVIDED BY USER
When the User registers for and/or use the Service User provide Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP with full name, age, physical data, training level, and and-mail.
When the User uses Services, the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may collect User’s weight, height, health conditions, and injuries.
1.2.	Data provided by third parties
When the User decides to log in using a third party service similar to (Google, Facebook, and Twitter) Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP gets personal data from respective User’s account. This includes User’s age and name. Unless User choses to opt out on the login screen, Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP will also collect other data, such as email address. For more information, please refer to the policies of third party services chosen for log in.
1.3.	Data collected automatically:
1.3.1.	Reference data
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP collect data about User’s referring to Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP or URL. It may be the app or place on the Web where User were when were tapped on Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP’s advertisement.
1.3.2.	Advertising ID’s
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP collects User’s Apple Identifier for advertising (“IDFA”) or Google Advertising ID (“AAID”) (depending on the operating system of User’s device). User can typically reset these numbers through the settings of User’s device’s operating system (but Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP does not control this).
1.3.3.	Device and Location data.
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP collects data from User’s mobile device. Examples of such data include: device settings, model of a device, hardware ID, operating system, language settings, IP address, time zone, Internet service provider, mobile carrier, Facebook ID, Google ID, and Twitter ID.
1.3.4.	Usage data
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP records how the User interacts with the Service. For example, Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP logs
 User’s taps on certain areas of the interface,  features, and content the User interacts with, how often User use the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP. User’s training program progress, trainings User do, the time and duration of User’s trainings, how long User is in the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP and User’s subscription orders. Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP also record the advertising in Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP with which User interact (and links to which those advertising lead).
1.3.5.	Apple's Health App and the Apple HealthKit API 
Users may authorize Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP to synchronize training information and collect information from Apple iOS Health App Data. The user can decide what information is placed into the Health App. Users can also modify which specific data Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP can collect and access through Health App settings. Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP request access to User’s weight, heart rate, and active energy burned. Additionally, Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP requests permission to write info to active energy burned and training type. User Health App Data is considered personally identifiable data. The information provided directly in the Health App (i.e., not through Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP) is governed by the Apple Terms and Conditions and Privacy Policy. Personal Information from the Health App is not shared by Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP to third parties for the purpose of advertising or other use-based data mining purposes other than improving health, or for the purpose of health research. 
1.3.6.	Location Information. 
If the User has enabled location services on mobile device, Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP collects location information to calculate quantity of steps in a day, running length, and reading the miles with voice. User can disable location services on his phone. 
2.	PURPOSES FOR COLLECTION OF PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA
2.1.	Provision of Service
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP collects personally identifiable data to provide service to its User’s. It includes enabling the User to use the Service in a seamless manner and preventing or addressing service errors or technical issues.
2.2.	Communication regarding use of Service
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may communicate with User’s by push notifications or e-mails. Such communicating may include motivational messages and reminders encouraging the User to follow training plan, or other information about the Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP. Users may receive a push notification every day at a particular time reminding to train. User may also opt out of receiving push notifications by changing the settings on the mobile device.
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may collect data concerning the date and time when the message was viewed by User, as well as when User interacted with it, such as by clicking on links included in the message. 
2.3.	Customization of User’s experience
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP processes User’s personally through identifiable data, such as physical characteristics, to adjust the content of the Service and make offers tailored to User’s personal preferences. Due to such processing, users get access, for example, to a personal injury sport injuries program.
2.4.	Management of accounts and provision of customer support
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP processes User’s personally identifiable data to respond to User’s requests for technical support, service information or to any other communication the  user initiates. This includes accessing User’s account to address technical support requests. Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may send User notifications or emails about the performance of Service, security, payment transactions, notices regarding Terms of Service or this Privacy Policy.
2.5.	Sending of marketing communications
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP processes User’s personally identifiable data for marketing purposes. The User may receive information about products, such as for example, special offers. 
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may also show advertisements and send push notifications for marketing purposes. To opt out of receiving push notifications, User need to change the settings on device.
2.6.	Personalization of marketing
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP use User’s personally identifiable data to tailor advertising and possibly show them to User at the relevant time. 
User may opt out or influence personalized advertising by editing following settings.
iOS: Go to “Settings,” then “Privacy” and tap “Advertising” to select “Limit Ad Track”. Also User can reset advertising identifier in the same section.
Android: Open the Google Settings, tap “Ads” and enable “opt out of interest-based ads”. User can reset advertising identifier in the same section.
Google Ads is an advertisings delivery service provided by Google. It allows Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP to tailor the way the advertisements appear. For example, show an advertisement to users who have purchased a subscription. Some other examples of events that may be used for tailoring advertisings includes, installing Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP, finishing a training session or training program. Google allows its users to opt out of Google’s personalized ads and to prevent their data from being used by Google Analytics.
2.7.	To enforce our Terms of Service and to prevent and combat fraud
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP uses personal data to enforce agreements and contractual commitments, to detect, prevent, and combat fraud. Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may share User’s information with others, including law enforcement agencies (in particular, if a dispute arises in connection with Terms of Use).
2.8.	Researching and analyzing of use of the Service
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP performs researching and analyzing to, maintain, improve, innovate, plan, design, analyze operations, and to modernize Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP. This data is also used to test and improve offers, for statistical analysis purposes. It allows to better understand what features and training plans of Users like more, what categories of Users use Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP. 
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP uses Google Analytics to help analyze how Users use it. Google Analytics for mobile apps provides a platform to measure User interactions. This tool allowing Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP to better understand and optimize User’s engagement with application. 
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP use Fabric, which is an analytics service provided by Crashlytics, a business division of Google. 



2.9.	To comply with legal obligations
Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP may process, use, or share User’s data when the law requires it, in particular, if a law enforcement agency requests particular User’s data by available legal means.
