10.	CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS
California’s Shine the Light law gives California residents the right to ask companies once a year what personal information they share with third parties for those third parties' direct marketing purposes. Learn more about what is considered to be personal information under the statute.
If User is a California resident, Smart Fitness or one of the private branding of SMART WORKOUT APP will provide the requested information to respective User email address. To obtain this information from lease User may send an email message to smartfitness7@gmail.com which includes “Request for California Privacy Information” on the subject line and state of residence.
Notice: not all information sharing is covered by the “Shine the Light” requirements and only information on covered sharing will be included in response.
